        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi> </placeName>
                    <placeName>[2 Bryanston Street, London]</placeName>
                    <date>Jan. 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1877</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for your kind offer, which w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be of great value to anyone engaged in embryological studies, but as this is not the case with me, I will not accept your kindness<ref target="#foot.f1"/> &amp; remain | Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Miller’s letter has not been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
